---
import PrivacyDoc from '@/layouts/PrivacyDoc.astro';
import { apps } from '@/data/apps';

const app = apps.find((a) => a.id === 'tendly')!;
---

<PrivacyDoc app={app}>
  <p>
    Tendly is a care task and reminder app. This Privacy Policy explains how Tendly handles
    information when you use the app.
  </p>

  <h2>Information Tendly Handles</h2>
  <p>
    Tendly is designed to keep your care data on your device. Depending on how you use the app,
    Tendly may handle:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      Care task details, such as task titles, categories, notes, repeat schedules, due dates, and
      completion history.
    </li>
    <li>
      Optional photos that you add from your camera or photo library for tasks or task completions.
    </li>
    <li>App preferences, such as your selected language.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How Information Is Used</h2>
  <p>Tendly uses this information only to provide app functionality, including:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Showing and organizing your care tasks.</li>
    <li>Calculating upcoming, due, and overdue reminders.</li>
    <li>Displaying completion history and basic statistics.</li>
    <li>Saving your selected app language.</li>
    <li>Showing task or completion photos inside the app.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Data Storage</h2>
  <p>
    Tendly stores task data, completion logs, and preferences locally on your device using app
    storage. Photos that you add are copied into Tendly's private app documents storage on your
    device.
  </p>
  <p>
    The current version of Tendly does not send your task data, notes, photos, completion history,
    or language preference to Codeek servers.
  </p>

  <h2>Data Sharing</h2>
  <p>Tendly does not sell your personal information.</p>
  <p>
    The current version of Tendly does not share your task data, notes, photos, completion history,
    or language preference with third parties.
  </p>
  <p>
    The app includes placeholder interfaces for features such as Google Calendar export, AI advice,
    and local reminders. These integrations are not active in the current version. If these features
    are enabled in a future version, this Privacy Policy should be updated before release to explain
    what data is accessed, collected, used, or shared.
  </p>

  <h2>Permissions</h2>
  <p>
    Tendly may ask for permission to access your camera or photo library when you choose to add a
    photo. These permissions are used only for the photo action you request.
  </p>
  <p>
    Tendly does not require broad file access. Photos selected or captured through the app are stored
    in Tendly's app-specific storage.
  </p>

  <h2>Data Retention and Deletion</h2>
  <p>
    Tendly keeps your task data and photos on your device until you edit or delete them in the app,
    remove app data from your device settings, or uninstall the app.
  </p>
  <p>
    Uninstalling Tendly may remove locally stored app data, depending on your device and backup
    settings.
  </p>

  <h2>Security</h2>
  <p>
    Tendly relies on the security protections provided by your device operating system and
    app-specific storage. You are responsible for keeping your device, screen lock, and backups
    secure.
  </p>

  <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
  <p>
    Tendly is not directed to children under 13. Tendly does not knowingly collect personal
    information from children.
  </p>

  <h2>International Users</h2>
  <p>
    Your information is stored locally on your device. If future versions add cloud, calendar, AI, or
    other external integrations, data handling may depend on the services you choose to connect.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
  <p>
    This Privacy Policy may be updated when Tendly changes. The updated version should include a new
    effective date.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>Contact email: <code>enesk6u@gmail.com</code></p>
</PrivacyDoc>
